This repository provides the implementation of the VC-Eq-PBCD algorithm and the VC-PBCD algorithm for solving the user equilibrium traffic assignment problem. The code is intended to support reproducibility, algorithm comparison, and further research in large-scale traffic assignment.

The project includes:
- C++ implementations of VC-Eq-PBCD and VC-PBCD
- Network data files for several benchmark transportation networks
- Reference implementations or source folders for comparison methods, including Eq-PBCD, iGP, iGreedy, and iTAPAS
- Result files and related experimental outputs

The raw transportation network data used in this project were obtained from the Transportation Networks repository maintained by Bar-Gera (bstabler/TransportationNetworks).

The algorithmic framework and numerical results are described in:

Zhang, K., Liu, Z., Zhang, H., Zhang, Y., Tang, Y. M., & Fu, X. (2026). A graph vertex-coloring-based parallel block coordinate descent method for solving the traffic assignment problem. Transportation Research Part C: Emerging Technologies, 183, 105439.

Requirements:
- C++11-compatible compiler
- OpenMP support
- VScode
- Windows environment is assumed in the provided project configuration

Compilation example:
- g++ -o VC-Eq-PBCD -std=c++11 -fopenmp VC-Eq-PBCD.cpp 

Example execution:
- .\VC-Eq-PBCD.exe 3 24 1600 3 8 2 1 1 1 1 1 1 1

For questions regarding implementation, usage, or data access, please contact Kai Zhang at zhang_kai_frank@163.com.
